<subSubSection id="51BDEE0BA549CAF6FD6E10A3C3E763A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4CBD16DF7D3A88030C53A90554527BB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5400D662A9EFF1E89FF24348428D54E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
A common and widespread species of the subantarctic forests and moorlands of the Magallanes and 
<normalizedToken id="C2431AE477FE6AD0E4E7476FD2F3B99A" originalValue="Aisén">Aisen</normalizedToken>
Regions on damp to wet soil, fallen logs, and tree stumps (
<bibRefCitation id="D07C12B4EB03DF1D91550EA49F6857F4" author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="11 - 47" refId="B18" refString="Ochi, H, 1982. A revision of the Bryoideae (Musci) in southern South America. Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University. Nature and Science 31: 11 - 47" title="A revision of the Bryoideae (Musci) in southern South America. Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University." volume="31" year="1982">Ochi 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Reports from further north are likely misidentifications and are either 
<taxonomicName id="9CE9C46447AEC58733256BC70118215A" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. andicola" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="andicola">
<emphasis id="9648B536377E3724A6A33C021AB06FB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. andicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="8FF3F573E079A6E8404FF6FEE2FA0012" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis id="419393852C6F98324728BC94A3F685C6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is a robust species with dioicous sexual condition, rosulate stems, sometimes with 2+ interrupted clumps along stems, large leaves that are contorted to somewhat imbricate when dry, serrulate distal leaf margins, an extremely wide limbidium of 4+ rows distally, and brown to red-brown rhizoidal tubers. The wide limbidium often gives the leaves a white-margined appearance. The species is also found in Argentina, the Falkland Islands, and extreme southern New Zealand (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation id="DAFB47EA3F6274B510E434748FB66B49" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" author="Mohamed, MA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="401 - 465" refId="B12" refString="Mohamed, MA, 1979. A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species. Journal of Bryology 10 (4): 401 - 465, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" title="A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" volume="10" year="1979">Mohamed 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 422, as 
<taxonomicName id="6C27EA964CC625DB6651F44E885C559A" authorityName="Cardot" authorityYear="1905" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis id="33B5A98169F327F6DCC53C35E1F7B6FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Bryum perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="61E9CB94E1980B3269300042DA8FF369" author="Fife, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" publicationUrl="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" refId="B4" refString="Fife, AJ, 2015. Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N.Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at: https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" title="Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N. Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at:" url="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" year="2015">Fife 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 87, as 
<taxonomicName id="4B994751C0295C85C35FA12761C54A85" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis id="6622EC043CB18CB51F5F2026B594C0FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
